<br>
One of the big negatives, to me, is that all the adventures require fixed groups for fixed periods of time.  It really makes it tough when someone in the group has an emergency, or gets called to dinner, or whatever, because you can't replace them.<br>
<br>
I also don't like the idea that all the adventures are time trials.  The reason, I suppose, is that mobs don't respawn, so it would be trivially easy if you could take forever to do it.  But couldn't they have put in some adventures with respawning mobs and less of a &quot;beat the clock&quot; element?<br>
<br>
Really, all of LDoN is just like an extended version of the PoJ trials.<br>
<br>
