 for 25k-30k in a time when the inflation rate was much lower.  When you got a group in zones like Old Sebilis you knew you had a shot at scoring uber loots that you were actually very proud to wear because they were the best available in the game.<br>
<br>
Another thing was the sense of fear and exploration.  EQ has become so old people come to expect certain things.  Most of us already have the basic gameplay logics down to a science.  To be honest Old Sebilis was creepy for a while until people on Saryrn started to flood it during Velious.  The mobs there were tough for its time.<br>
<br>
Overall I think LDON is ok.  At this stage in the game unless they put plane of time type loots on normal 1 group doable mobs in zones like the plane of fire or bastion of thunder I don't think EQ can ever return to that original phase of the game.  There's way too many powergamers now and the &quot;phat lewtz&quot; have gone from a soloable drop, to a 1 group doable drop, to a several group doable drop and now to a 72-100 man army required drop.  There won't be much of a sense of mystery either.  People have broken this game's mechanic down into little pieces and shared it with everyone else.  The best aspect of LDON I guess is the fact that Necromancers rule and the little sense of fear of losing in one of those adventure trials. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=452034"><br>
