<br>
But I kinda like the fixed duration and the intensive pace. It's nice to log on, make a group and know that you can complete &quot;something&quot; consequential in EQ in 90 minutes (or less, ideally.) The non-stop pace keeps an element of excitement, again reminiscent of the Trials.<br>
<br>
Yeah, it makes sense to take bio breaks and get snacks and drinks BEFORE entering the LDoN dungeon. I have no problem with this. One of the worst problems with pickup groups is when you get a cleric, chanter, tank or whatever who keeps going afk &quot;for a minute&quot;, and comes back 5 minutes later. And then repeats this every 15 minutes. Anybody doing this in LDoN is probably not going to get too many groups down the road. Justifiably.<br>
<br>
My biggest gripe about LDoN is that groups pretty much HAVE to have a cleric or 90-rez paladin because not many people are willing to eat more than 1 un-rezzed death in a crawl. Kinda limits group construction options... particularly when it comes to primary healers.<br>
<br>
Not sure what they could have done about this, other than permit clerics to zone in just to rez. LOL <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=herrickreigns>Herrick Reigns</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 549<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(9/15/03 9:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3544.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LoY</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The best aspect of LDON I guess is the fact that Necromancers rule and the little sense of fear of losing in one of those adventure trials.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
